      "writtenOn": "2017-12-21T20:25:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is the value that sigsetjmp() will return when coming out of this siglongjmp(). You can’t use 0 because then you won’t be able to distinguish the return from the sigsetjmp() when setting up the jump from the return when a signal was raised and handled.\n\nThis makes it seem like this wasn’t fully tested. At least locally, you should force yourself into the K branch and raise(SIGFPE) before the dlsym() call. Test that without sigaction() first to establish that you can get a crash, and then again with sigaction() to establish that you’re able to catch it and proceed normally.",
